    {
      "para_id": "Q000872.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(1) For Ninhursaĝa , the mother of the gods , Lu-Utu , governor of Umma , built a temple on her beloved square for his well-being . He made its foundation unblemished . He drove in its foundation pegs , and within it he put its divine powers in good order ."
    }
  ],
